cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of adaptive trajectory tracking control for a class of nonlinear systems with parametric uncertainties. The proposed approach involves designing a robust nonlinear state feedback and augmenting it with a model-free learning algorithm to estimate the model uncertainties. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.SY is the most likely category as the paper deals with control systems, while cs.LG and cs.RO are also likely categories as the paper involves learning algorithms and robot manipulators.
